input_doc:
I have heard sooo many good things about this place and was really looking forward to it. We got there at 2pm on a Saturday and there was STILL a long line, so I was pretty convinced this would really impress me.

I got the chorizo queso to start off with and it was absolutely delicious, so all good there. But then I got my tacos and was disappointed. The hot chicken taco tasted nothing like hot chicken and had a weird flavor. The adobo chicken had a very basic flavor to it, indistinguishable from the shredded chicken you find at any local Mexican restaurant. Both tortillas were hard in odd places.

Maybe I should've gotten something that wasn't chicken, I don't know. But based on what I had, I can't understand the hype behind this place. If you want something similar but better, I recommend hitting up Local Taco.

input_doc: The new spot that just opened up. Figured I'd give it a try,  regrettably, I must say,  should've made a different choice. First, I had to drive back and get the right burger, because instead of a mushroom swiss with jalapenos and bacon, they made a jalapeno burger, which did not look very appetizing... Upon returning home with the correct burger, I open it up to find half cooked bacon, which I just disposed of. Upon my first bite, it was a mix between soggy mush bun and a very flat grey looking patty. My wife at half of hers and couldn't even finish because ot felt like pure "gut bomb" as she called it. Overall, my experience was very ehhh, "not so good" burger. Also, perhaps they should invest in better staff.

I have lived in Santa Barbara all my life and have always heard people talking about Tinker's. I have never eaten here before till this past week and wow I have been missing out!! 
This place is amazing!! The employees are very nice, and the food is delicious. 
Very good locals hole-in-the-wall spot but if you are in the area defiantly give it a try Tinker's is one of the restaurants that Summerland is known for. Anytime you see locals flocking to the same spot over again that's how you know it's a real winner!
Does not disappoint if you are looking for a great burger and shake check it out and see how amazing it is for yourself!!!

The gator bites had a slight heat, the burgers were tasty and the fries with beans and sour cream and chili were to die for. input_doc:
Datz is great, I've eaten here twice and mainly wanted to come back to try the donuts! THEY'RE A MUST!

I ordered 1 Nutella, 1 maple bacon and 1 Oreo-all were delicious but my fianc ate his at home so they had been out for some time and were a little dry.

All the food is great as well, I ordered the Sriracha sammie, my friend got the Popeyes rise n shiner Sammie w/ avocado-the bartender mentioned it's better that way and it was, and the fianc got the pork chops, all were great.
I've also had their gigantic hot chocolate which is sooooo good...I clearly have a sweet tooth) and another item that's no longer on the menu, but it was good as well.

Basically go, you won't be disappointed!

input_doc: We were recently in Tucson & decided to try U.S. Fries. I am so glad that we did. It is soooo fricking delicious. At our table we had a traditional, pulled pork & vegetarian poutine as well as a cheeseburger. Oh my goodness. They were all amazing, especially the pulled pork. We will definitely be back when we are within a 50 mile radius. The french fries were crispy, the gravy was savory and the cheese curds are spot on. To top it all off, the restaurant is clean & the staff is friendly.

input_doc: I called like 20 mins before closing and i was hoping they were still serving people. luckily they were , the phone call was lovely and made me excited to go get my food. i got a 10 piece hot wings with blue cheese. that's about the only wing flavor i eat so i've tried plenty of wings and these are BY FAR the best i've had. juicy, fat (really good pieces of chicken)  and seasoned!! i can't stress enough how seasoned the actual chicken is. the first two pieces didn't have a lot of  hot sauce on it but it was still soo good i didn't mind if i didn't have hot sauce , even the blue cheese was good. overall 11/10. i will be back the restaurant is literally under 5 mins from me sooooo i'll be back ;)

input_doc:
Went there for lunch for the first time today with a couple ladies from the South City Girls Meetup Group. Service was terrific from the hostess, to the busser, to the server (Marcus). I had the Prosperity Club with sweet potato chips and they were sooo delicious! My companions had the beer cheese soup and the Hummus Three Ways. I will definitely recommend Alumni next time my workplace does a lunch out celebration. 

On a side note, I see in the reviews that dinner isn't as successful for people as it is for their lunch customers. Don't know why, different staff/managers, maybe? Plus, their person who comments on people's reviews needs to switch the comments up and also address the dissatisfied customers. It comes across as superficial otherwise. Just my thoughts as I was reading through.

input_doc:
I spent many saturdays walking here with my folks to shop and eat breakfast...  I still go every time I'm in Philthy to gets my grub on.

Harry Ochs - Best Butcher in the world

Amish Breakfasts - Ummm scrapple and pancakes

Amish sticky buns - No raisins please, get these at the Amish bakery or at the breakfast stand.  Hands down best baked good in the world - Tartine's morning buns are a distant second

DeNic's - My favorite sammie in the galaxy is the roast pork, all garlicy and nice - with aged provolone and peppers

Birch Beer - Homebrew from the Amish, sweet!

Just about anything at Delilahs...

Down Home Diner and Jack McDavid - Because you made fun of Bobby Flay years before it became fashionable!  

And all the rest of youse there....

input_doc:
This place is by far the best if you're looking for a tasty burger that melts in your mouth. I ordered the 500 burger and added a side of wild boar bacon. The meat was so tender and it wasn't medium rare like I asked but somehow, it was still tender. There are many sauces to choose from such as sirracha and a house sauce( yogurt and horseradish) and spicy barbecue sauce.
 
I would have given this place 5 stars, but I was dissatisfied with the size of the restaurant. It's sooo tiny and on a crowded day you might have to eat outside!! But the biggest con were the Fries!!! They looked good but tasted greasy and as if they were old and reheated. I should have gotten the sweet potato fries. It's a good thing I brought home a side of sauce so I can dredge the fries in it!

input_doc:
Had a date night here with the boyfriend on Friday.  Was originally looking to take him to the Irish Fionn McCool's, and realized that Fionn's had been replaced.  This Chatham is a HUGE step up from its Mass Ave counterpart.  Higher class clientele and the bar and service staff is a step up as well.  The hostess stand is a group of young high school aged gabbers, but hey, its what I did then too!
He had the heart stopper, a burger with a fried egg and 2 patties, He had to take it apart to eat and loved it!  I had the black and blue, cooked to order, tender and juicy, not a big fan of rasher bacon, but I really enjoyed it!
Jeff our server was very energetic and welcoming and gave his honest auggestions about what to and not to order by his recommendations!
Will go back, but not in a big rush to do so!!!

input_doc:
First, this restaurant is a bit of a cross between a stop-in Chinese joint (numbered meals on the wall) and an American "family restaurant". There are a few tables and the waiter/cook will take your order and bring you food tableside. Ambiance is not exotic or impressive, however - the food is fresh and delish!
I had the chicken shawarma platter and picked rice and baba ganouj for the sides. The baba was very smooth and smoky - exactly what you would expect and you get a TON of chicken and rice (got two meals out if it) plus a large pita comes with the meal. I wanted grape leaves - they only do a full order - but they roll them there and they are delish - so it was worth it!
All in all, not fancy, but very yummy.  Mmmmm shawarma...

input_doc: Ordered delivery via GrubHub tonight.  Reasonable time for the distance.  At first glance we were a little underwhelmed by the presentation and size (I know, I know it's small plates) but it was more than filling once we dug in!  The Bulgogi Chicken was sooo good, I don't even like chicken but I stole quite a few bites from hubs.  Pad Thai was very good, maybe not the absolute best I've had but super enjoyable.  However, OMG the chicken dumplings ARE the best I've ever had.  Absolutely stuffed with chicken filling and perfectly cooked.  We cannot wait to dine in and try more food and the drinks!

input_doc: If you want what just might be the best burger you have ever had, you need to try this place! I am a child of the 60's from Chicago. My Grandfather and Dad took us to places like this all the time. No frills, great atmosphere, service and food at a reasonable price. Our beer was served in frozen, heavy old goblet glasses of my past. We had double cheeseburgers, fried mushrooms and onion rings, all served in red plastic baskets lined with deli paper. Our server asked us if we had been there before. We had not so she gave us a brief menu tour. The menu is on an old board on the wall. Check out the pictures posted on their Yelp page to see what I am talking about!!!

input_doc:
This happened by accident. I have scathing for wet nuts on my waffle sundaes (walnuts soaked in vanilla syrup).  The only diner in the area I knew had them was closing as I walked in. After I recovered from the heart attack I had I called around and found this gem!

When you walk in they are all sooooo sweet and happy. The food at the other tables  looked fresh and amazing. All we got was the waffle sundae, bacon, corn beef hash, tea and cocoa but everything was perfect! The strawberries were fresh and the corned beef hash was one of the best I've had. Not too salty and crispy.
I can't wait to go back!

input_doc:
This is our go to Chinese take out. The dinner combinations are only available for take out... So when dining in you do not receive a chocho or fried rice- only white rice. Well goooood Lawd it was twice the amount of chicken I normally get in my take out I didn't even touch the rice. I enjoyed my pia colada and the won ton soup was the best I have ever had. 

I have enough chicken for two more meals from one $12 entree. My SO had left overs for an extra meal as well which is rare! So portions are huge! We agreed to share an entree next time we go.
